name: Canyon Matka
description: Picturesque gorge with medieval monasteries, also offering boating, hiking & cave exploration.

name: Old Bazaar
description: Vibrant old bazaar built in Ottoman architectural style, with mosques, markets, shops and cafes.

name: Kokino megalithic observatory
description: Mountainous site with the archaeological ruins of a Bronze Age observatory.

name: Stone Bridge
description: Built in the 15th century, this stone, arched bridge is a prominent symbol of the country's capital.

name: Monastery of St. Naum
description: Eastern Orthodox monastery founded in 905, open to the public with lake views & live peacocks.

name: Memorial House of Mother Teresa
description: Museum dedicated to a renowned Catholic nun, with an eclectic design & a striking, modern chapel.

name: National Park „Pelister“
description: Covering 66 sq .mi., this popular forest of rare pines offers trails, wildlife, ski areas & views.

name: Millennium Cross
description: Memorial cross on top of a mountain accessible by cable car, with picturesque views of city below.

name: The Bay of Bones
description: Reconstructed village of stilt houses displaying Bronze & Iron Age items recovered from Lake Ohrid.

name: Mavrovo National Park
description: Large national park founded in 1949, featuring trails through mountains & canyons & along a river.

name: Archaeological Museum of the Republic of Macedonia
description: Grand museum offering archeological relics from ancient Macedonian times, including coins & statues.

name: Church of Saint John the Theologian
description: Historic, landmark Orthodox church overlooking Lake Ohrid, with picnic & seating areas.

name: Skopje Fortress
description: Remains of a 6th-century hilltop stone fortress, offering panoramic views of the city & river.

name: Holy Mother of God (Treskavec Monastery)
description: Hilltop church dating from the 12th century, with elaborate ceiling frescoes & valley views.

name: „Plaoshnik“
description: This archeological site features a restored 9th-century church plus ruins from earlier structures.

name: Xhamia e Larme
description: Ottoman-era mosque rebuilt in the 1800s known for its frescoed facade & vivid painted interior.

name: Galičica National Park
description: Protected area around Mount Galicica, with rugged hiking & biking trails overlooking 2 vast lakes.

name: Macedonian Holocaust Museum
mk_name: Меморијален центар на холокаустот на Евреите од Македонија
description: Holocaust museum dedicated to Jewish Macedonian people in a contemporary building, open since 2011.

name: Museum of the Macedonian Struggle
mk_name: Музеј на македонската борба за самостојност
description: Stately museum showcasing scenes & artifacts from the Macedonian revolution for independence.

name: Skopje Zoo
description: Founded in 1926, the 12-hectare zoo houses many animal species, an educational center & a play area.

name: Bigorski Monastery St John the Baptist
description: Tranquil monastery founded in 1020 overlooking mountains & housing a collection of holy relics.

name: Museum of the Republic of Macedonia
description: National museum dedicated to the archeological, ethnological & historic heritage of Macedonia.

name: Stobi
description: Conserved archaeological site consisting of a Paeonian city that was later conquered by Macedonians.

name: Museum of Contemporary Art
description: Bright, airy museum housing modern & contemporary works by Macedonian & international artists.

name: Church of Saints Clement and Panteleimon
description: The most sacred in the region, this ancient Byzantine church sits on a hill overlooking the lake.

name: Museum of the City of Skopje
description: Housed in a former railway station, this museum features exhibitions on the city's history.

name: Suli An
description: Grand 15th-century caravansarai, now housing a local-history museum & Academy of Arts.

name: Church of Saint Sophia
description: Built in the Middle Ages, this Macedonian Orthodox Church displays centuries-old religious art.

name: St. Panteleimon
description: Compact, Byzantine-era church dating to 1164, known for its colorful medieval frescoes.

name: Vodno
description: 1,066-m. mountain featuring hiking, churches, the Millennium Cross, the Prskalo waterfall & more.

name: Lake Ohrid
description: This large ancient lake straddling the border between Albania & Macedonia reaches a depth of 300m.

name: Saint Joachim Osogovski
description: Orthodox monastery & church complex with elaborate frescoes, a natural spring & a restaurant.

name: Lake Matka
description: Man-made lake in a scenic canyon, stocked for fishing & with an underwater cave.

name: The Bridge of Civilisations in Macedonia
Gërmia Park
description: Sprawling regional park with pine forests, multi-use trails, a seasonal swimming pool & restaurants.

name: Prizren Fortress
description: Once the capital of the Serbian Empire, this medieval fortress is built on a hill with scenic views.

name: NEWBORN
description: Contemporary monument commemorating Kosovo's declaration of independence from Serbia.

name: Mother Teresa Cathedral
description: Elegant, Romanesque-style cathedral built in honor of St. Teresa of Calcutta & inaugurated in 2010.

name: Dojran Lake
description: Picturesque lake bordered by national parkland, featuring trails alongside abundant flora & fauna.

name: Voras Ski Center (Kaimaktsalan)
description: Ski area topping 2,500 meters with lessons, a cafe & a small white chapel at the summit.

name: Lake Prespa
description: Picturesque freshwater lake bordered by national parkland, offering trails & abundant flora & fauna.

name: Treska
description: Macedonian river, a tributary of the Vardar, with 3 dams & lakes along its 132-km. course.

name: Rila Monastery
description: Ornate monastery, one of the country's most-visited cultural sites, with a museum & frescoes.

name: Kaneo
description: Tiny, rocky beach on Lake Ohrid featuring traditional seafood restaurants & a swimming platform.

name: Arcturos Bear Sanctuary
mk_name: Κέντρο Προστασίας Αρκούδας - Bear Conservation Area

name: Vlatadon Monastery
description: Hilltop Byzantine temple with city views, centuries-old frescoes, icons & religious treasures.

name: Mr. Bricolage
mk_name: Трговски центар со опрема за дома „Бриколаж“

name: BUNK'ART
description: Former Cold War bunker, now an underground contemporary art & history museum over several floors.

name: Castle of Kruja
description: Historic castle that houses several museums, the Tekke of Dollmë monument & the ruins of a mosque.

name: Skopje City Mall
description: Local staple for shopping & dining, with multiple levels of name-brand stores, cafes & a cinema.

name: Parku Rinia - Youth Park - Taiwan Park
description: Small park in the heart of Tirana featuring a large fountain & a pavilion with restaurants.

name: Ohrid St. Paul The Apostle Airport
